I’ve ordered delivery from here about 3 times now, and they have not disappointed. The fries are great and they give a lot, the pad Thai is fresh (although not as “traditional” as you may be used to if you’re an avid Thai food fan), the thai iced tea is also great (but can err on the sweet side if you like yours with less sugar). My go to dish would be the spicy basil, the flavor is perfect and the veggies are cooked excellently without being watered down or mushy. Want your food so spicy that your ancestors feel it? Just make a note when ordering and you shall get what you desire. It’s my favorite Thai place in the Bronx and I will be continuing to order from here when the craving strikes.

I ordered delivery on Doordash and the food cannot be worse. My order: Tom yum soup, Pineapple fried rice, pad thai, and fried wings. EVERYTHING tasted like SEA WATER. The cook must have mixed up sugar with salt. Pad thai was extremely wet and salty. Pineapple fried rice got some sweetness to it thanks to the pineapple which is the only reason why I gave 1 star (other than that’s the minimum). The worst thing was the tomyum soup and I’m not exaggerating when I say it’s just sea water.  I’ve had Thai food and Thai fusion countless times and this is by far the worst and most unauthentic. This is not Thai food. Periodt.

I get to eat here a lot since I work in the area. I have to say their service is always great and they keep the spot well organized consistently. Rates are convenient and they serve generous portions.

My husband and I decided to go here for our anniversary dinner last year. I was immediately disappointed when I saw how small the place was, as we were going with our 2 kids and honestly, I was expecting a “fancier” place. I couldn’t complain because I chose it after reading some reviews. But the man at the counter, who we later found out was the owner, was extremely friendly and they had SO many options on their menu. I love Thai food and I immediately knew what I wanted. The food was just amazing! We had great conversation with the owner and we tried to convince him to open up a new branch in Queens, because he’d definitely put the rest of the guys on Hillside out of business. He also gave us a complimentary fried ice cream when he found out it was our anniversary. I never got the opportunity to go back but I suddenly had a craving for Thai food and realized I never gave a review. I can’t wait to visit again!

This spot is my preferred one. I eat in a lot of restaurants but to this restaurant I  constantly return again and again. The stuff is very friendly and the cuisine they serve is so fresh and tasty. I never miss an opportunity to have a good meal in this place. I highly recommend this place.

Usually this place is great. I've never had an issue in the past, but yesterday I found several black hairs in my bright green sticky rice. I was completely grossed out. And I ordered an extra one for today - they both went right in the garbage. I will be contacting Grubhub for a refund because that was absolutely disgusting. I couldn't leave a review yesterday because I was getting nauseous every time I thought about it! Also, the delivery usually only takes about a half hour. They gave me an estimate of an hour or so. As soon as it hit the hour I received a call from the driver. Somehow he was using navigation, was only about 5 blocks away yet he couldn't find me. Or follow simple instructions to stay on the road he was on, drive 5 blocks until he reached a tall building. I live in a high rise building on a main service road. I'm the only building on this road. There are HUGE numbers with the building address right in front and it took him quite some time to find me. The only good thing I have to say about this experience is that I am disabled and many times the drivers don't want to come up to buildings because it isn't easy to park. However when we spoke on the phone I reminded him that my receipt stated that I was disabled and to please come up. He did not complain and he came right up to my door. I will take the chance and order from here again but if I ever find another hair in my food I will be calling the BBB, 311, and any and all agencies that regulate the restaurant business.

if i could give 10 stars i would. This place has renewed my love for Thai food. Local Thai in the Bronx is lacking, but I have found Shangri-La with this establishment. I was reticent to order at first, in fear of  possible disappointment,   The lunch specials brought an abundant selection of items to try and I was extremely satisfied with everything, even down to the salad dressing. At this point I would order anything on the menu and I can't wait to explore. Great Job!! As far as the Pad Thai goes, it wasn't typical. That doesn't mean it wasn't good. It seems as though many Chinese spots have it on their menu nowadays. If you want a more typical flavor, head in that direction. I enjoyed the refreshing change.

The soup and salad was good and the vegetable dumplings and shumai were especially great. I would definitely recommend that the pad thai recipe be improved upon.

Pretty disappointed with this place. Heard about it through word of mouth from some of friends and they claimed it was good, I saw a vegan part to the menu and decided to give it a try.  The food was bland, somewhat mediocre, tasteless, not spicy (I chose medium spice), and it wasn't nourishing or satisfying. Just seemed like slightly more expensive chinese food. The woman taking my order on the phone was obviously new. At the end of my order I give her my address and made sure to spell out my street name, then she tells me theres a $5 delivery charge, which I heard was based on distance and I'm only two neighborhoods (1.5 miles) away. I accepted it. Then she calls me back to confirm my street name. I confirm again and ask if everything is alright, in which she assured things were fine. Ten minutes later the delivery driver calls me asking to confirm my street name, in which I do. After he hangs up I call the store and speaking to the same woman I ask if there was a mistake on the delivery fee. She keeps saying no, rushing me off the phone, she keeps interrupting me by saying bye and she's inserting these sarcastic remarks as I'm trying to make sure of the situation. The food arrives an hour after ordering and the driver declares that there was a mistake in the delivery fee as the receipt reflects her mistake.  I'm going to learn from this mistake, next time I eat from a restaurant for the first time, I'm going to visit the place first. The food wasn't really worth the inconvenience.

I love the fact that there's finally a Thai place in the Bronx, especially a really good one! The food is great and the space is very cozy. They also always seem to have the right show or sports game on their screens and they'll change the channel for you if you ask. Their pineapple fried rice or pad Thai are my favorites.

Thai No. 1 proves to be a great addition to the Bronx's limited, but now growing selection of Thai food establishments. Though a bit more modest than Ceetay (in Mott Haven), Thai No. 1 still has a cozy, and rustic interior. Thai No. 1 offers traditional favorites and then some. I was excited to see that the menu has not only vegetarian options, but an entire Vegan section. When in doubt, the soba noodle soup is a safe and delicious choice. The staff is very friendly and accommodating. The owner treated us to free birthday cake during our first visit! The prices are very reasonable.

Foods decent but be careful ordering take out. They skim on portions during the week. I've consistently gotten half their normal entree sizes when ordering take out. If you're busy that's understandable take your time and cook the right portions. It's a joke when you're dropping 31 bucks and to get 19 dollars of food.
